	- Blockchain is a peer-to-peer, distributed ledger that is cryptographically-secure, append-only, immutable (extremely hard to change), and updateable only via consensus or agreement among peers.

	- Blockchain Systems Engineering => Information Security + Cryptography + Distributed Database Systems
	
	- A Smart Contract is a piece of codedeployed in the Blockchain node. Execution of a smart contract is initiated by a message embedded in a transaction

	- CAP Theorem => Consistency, Availability, Partioning.

	- Core Data Structures in Blockchain => Merkle Trees, Hash Functions , Hash Chains